# {{ eigenstate_ee_name }}

This directory is a rendered Ansible Builder context for an
`eigenstate.ipa` IdM execution environment.

Base image:

```text
{{ eigenstate_ee_base_image }}
```

Build:

```bash
ansible-builder build -t {{ eigenstate_ee_image }}
```

Smoke test from the collection checkout:

```bash
ansible-playbook playbooks/aap-ee-smoke.yml \
  -e eigenstate_ee_image={{ eigenstate_ee_image }}
```

Push after logging in with your container runtime:

```bash
podman tag {{ eigenstate_ee_image }} registry.example.com/automation/{{ eigenstate_ee_name }}:{{ eigenstate_ee_tag }}
podman push registry.example.com/automation/{{ eigenstate_ee_name }}:{{ eigenstate_ee_tag }}
```

Do not commit registry tokens, automation hub tokens, IPA passwords, keytabs,
vault passwords, or private keys into this directory. Keep them in Controller
credentials, local environment variables, or untracked configuration.

Expected AAP credential mounts:

- `/etc/ipa/ca.crt` for the IdM CA certificate
- `/runner/env/ipa/<principal>.keytab` for a service or admin keytab
- `KRB5CCNAME` only when your workflow manages a custom Kerberos cache

OpenShift, Kubernetes, and Controller collections are not included by default.
Enable them through the role variables when needed.
